===============================================================================
ATTACK / KILL
===============================================================================

SYNTAX:
  attack <target>
  kill <target>

DESCRIPTION:
  Initiate combat with a target. The combat system uses rounds and
  initiative to determine action order.

EXAMPLES:
  > attack goblin
  You attack the goblin!
  
  > kill orc
  You attack the orc!
  
  > attack Marcus
  You attack Marcus! (if you know their name)

COMBAT ROUND:
  Once combat begins:
  1. Initiative is rolled
  2. Actions execute in initiative order  
  3. Attacks are made with to-hit rolls
  4. Defenses (dodge/parry) are checked
  5. Damage is applied
  6. Round repeats until combat ends

YOUR ATTACKS:
  - Number of attacks per round based on your level & OCC
  - Attack bonus based on your stats and skills
  - Damage based on weapon and Strength
  - Critical hits on natural 20

COMBAT DEFENSES:
  autododge on/off  - Automatically dodge attacks
  autoparry on/off  - Automatically parry attacks
  
  You can also manually choose defenses during combat.

ENDING COMBAT:
  - Defeat all enemies
  - Flee successfully
  - Target flees
  - One side dies

FLEEING:
  flee  - Attempt to escape combat
  
  Success depends on your Speed vs. enemy Speed.

DEATH:
  If you die in combat:
  - You lose experience
  - You respawn at your recall point
  - Some equipment may be lost

NOTES:
  - 'attack' and 'kill' are the same command
  - You cannot attack in safe rooms (usually cities)
  - Some NPCs are aggressive and will attack on sight
  - PvP (player vs player) combat requires consent (see 'help pvp')
  - Combat can be lethal - be prepared!

STRATEGY:
  - Check enemy difficulty before attacking
  - Use appropriate weapons and armor
  - Manage your PPE (magic) and ISP (psionics)
  - Team up for tough enemies
  - Know when to flee

===============================================================================
See also: help combat, help flee, help equipment, help skills
===============================================================================
